<topic id="steps">
  <title>Steps to execute cnode pass</title>
  
  <body>


    <p>  Followings are the steps that will be followed in the order to execute cnode pass scripts: </p>
	<p>
 <ol>
        <li>	cnode pass the script requires following arguments described below:
		<ol>
		
		
		<li><b>--settings_file: </b>
		This argument requires an input of settings file name. The file contains all the parameters described in the parameter section in above section.
<b>Where to find this file:</b> This file comes with script software package cloned from github repository. 
The file contains default values for standard Dell RedHat NFV solution 6.0.		</li>
		<li><b>	--ucrc:</b> Under Cloud RC files, it contains the authentication URL and credentials for Under Cloud Director node.
<b>Where to find this file:</b>
</li>
		<li><b>	--ocrc: </b>Over Cloud RC files, it contains the authentication URL and credentials for Over Cloud OpenStack environment.
<b>Where to find this file:</b> 
</li>


<li><b>--script_pass:</b> This arguments describes the type of pass mode to execute the scripts.
 Following 2 modes are applicable for input:
   <ol><li>cnode</li>
   <li>instance</li> </ol>
 </li>
		</ol>
		</li>


		<li> Run script through following command:
		
python enable_sriov.py --settings_file= settings file name> -â€“ucrc undersloud RC file name> --ocrc overcloud RC file name> --script_pass cnode 
<b>Example:</b> 

python enable_sriov.py --settings_file=sriov_settings_pass-cnode.ini --ucrc=stackrc --ocrc=r141rc --script_pass=cnode  

		</li>
		
		
		
		
		
</ol>
	  </p>
	  </body>
